15 "§52.2. Critical incident review team
16 A. Each child fatality and near fatality substantiated by the department
17 as being the result of abuse or neglect shall be reviewed by the critical incident
18 review team, hereinafter referred to as the review team. Any child fatality or
19 near fatality that was unsubstantiated by the department as being the result of
20 abuse or neglect may be reviewed by the review team at the discretion of the
21 chair of the review team.
22 B. The review team shall consist of the following members:
23 (1) The secretary of the Department of Children and Family Services, or
24 his designee.
25 (2) The chief medical director of the Department of Children and Family
26 Services, or his designee.
27 (3) A representative of the Department of Justice designated by the
28 attorney general.
29 (4) A representative of the office of state police designated by the
30 superintendent of state police.
31 (5) A representative of the Louisiana Department of Health designated
32 by the secretary of the Louisiana Department of Health.
33 (6) A coroner or forensic pathologist appointed by the president of the
34 Louisiana State Coroner's Association.
35 (7) A representative of a child advocacy center designated by the
36 Louisiana Alliance of Children's Advocacy Centers.
37 (8) The state child ombudsman, or his designee.
38 (9) A quality-improvement or continuous-improvement employee of the
39 Department of Children and Family Services with training in safety science or
40 human-factors analysis appointed by the secretary of the department.
41 C.(1) The representative of the Department of Justice designated by the
42 attorney general shall serve as the chair of the review team.
43 (2) The representative of the chair shall direct and coordinate meetings
44 of the review team.
